headline: CSX Stock Rises After Earnings Miss Estimates. It’s the Outlook.
summary: Shares rose in late trading on Thursday after the railroad posted solid fourth-quarter numbers.  Wall Street analysts tracked by FactSet were looking for EPS of 41 cents from sales of $3.5 billion.  Volumes rose 1% year over year, boosted by intermodal volumes.

headline: The Bull Case For Norfolk Southern (NSC) Could Change Following New East Edge Double-Stack Corridor Launch
summary: Norfolk Southern has launched East Edge, a newly cleared double-stack intermodal corridor between Chicago and New England that cuts transit times by up to 10 hours and replaces an older single-stack route with a higher-capacity, modernized line into Ayer, Massachusetts. This corridor materially expands the railroad’s ability to move containers through New England’s primary intermodal hub, potentially easing long-standing freight bottlenecks tied to e-commerce and distribution demand. headline: Norfolk Southern orders first new locomotives since 2022
summary: Norfolk Southern has acquired 40 new diesel-electric locomotives from Wabtec, its first such purchase since 2022, as it modernizes its fleet. The post Norfolk Southern orders first new locomotives since 2022 appeared first on FreightWaves.
